- **UI/Menu Implementation**
  - **Main Menu:**
    - Presents game title, start, and story mode (locked/unlocked).
    - Use clear navigation and highlight for selected options.
    - Play navigation and select sounds for feedback.
  - **Game Over Screen:**
    - Show final score, option to restart or return to main menu.
    - Use large, readable fonts and clear button prompts.
  - **Navigation:**
    - Support keyboard and joystick input for all menus.
    - Use visual feedback (highlight, color) for current selection.
    - Play sound on navigation and selection.
  - **Best Practices:**
    - Keep UI logic separate from game state and rendering.
    - Use constants for all font sizes, colors, and sound paths.
    - Make all menus extensible for new options or modes.
    - Ensure accessibility (readable fonts, color contrast).

- **DO:**
  - Use sound and visual feedback for all menu actions.
  - Keep UI code modular and easy to update.
  - Use consistent font and color schemes across screens.

- **DON'T:**
  - Hardcode UI strings or values in multiple places.
  - Mix menu logic with gameplay logic.
  - Omit feedback for navigation or selection.

